Exercise 1

Exercise 2

The plot looks like the head of a dinosaur. The correlation ceofficient is -0.0645.

Exercise 3

Create the data set star:

star_data <- datasaurus_dozen %>% filter(dataset=="star")

Plot the data:

ggplot(data=star_data, mapping=aes(x=x, y=y))+geom_point()

Find the correlation coefficient:

star_data %>% summarise(r=cor(x,y))
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##         r
##     <dbl>
## 1 -0.0630

The correlation coefficient is -0.0630

Exercise 5

Plot the data:

ggplot(data = datasaurus_dozen, aes(x = x, y = y, color = dataset)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ dataset, ncol = 3) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")

Find the correlation coefficient:

datasaurus_dozen %>%
  group_by(dataset) %>%
  summarize(r = cor(x, y)) %>%
  print(13)
## # A tibble: 13 x 2
##    dataset          r
